@node menu "Main Menu of AmiChannel News"
                           AmiChannel News - Issue 19
                                  March 2000

        The fast magazine in ENGLISH about all the news in the AMIGA world
    ______
---| MENU |---------------------------------------------------------------------
    ¯¯¯¯¯¯
   * @{" EDITORIAL : LARGER THAN LIFE " Link editorial}

     The monthly editor's thoughts by the editor. This time about the rise and
     fall of Phase 5.

   * @{" FLEECY DISCLOSE SOME INTERESTING NEWS " Link fleecy}

     The last conference of Fleecy in the AmigaZone chat area held on the
     evening of February 23, 2000, was a little bit boring because there were
     not a lot of people asking questions to Fleecy. Anyway, he disclosed some
     interesting things about the future.

   * @{" INTENT(TM) FONT SYSTEM FOR TAO'S DIGITAL CONTENT HEAVEN " Link tao}

     The Tao Group has announced the Tao's intent Font System. intent is Tao's
     binary portable applications layer for networked digital appliances,
     combining the most advanced technologies for an integrated Java(TM)
     language, C and portable assembler environment.

   * @{" PAGAN GAMES: UPDATE ON DEVELOPMENT PROGRESS " Link pagan}

     Pagan Games, developers of Dafel Bloodline and other games, report about
     the development of their projects.

   * @{" A.C.T. AND ISM TO COOPERATE FOR MULTI MEDIA PROJECTS " Link act}

     Two well known former Amiga companies, A.C.T. and ISM have reached a deal
     to cooperate for multi media projects for the new Amiga.

   * @{" AMIGA, INC. TO RELOCATE HEADQUATERS TO QUADRANT'S " Link quadrant}

     The Quadrant Corporation, developer of the business park, announced that
     Amiga moved its world headquarters to Snoqualmie Ridge on March 1.

   * @{" THE WORLD FOUNDRY: MARCH 2000 UPDATE " Link twf}

     Check the TWF March 2000 Update for the latest news about their upcomming
     games Explorer 2260 and Maim & Mangle.

   * @{" IREC FOR AMIGAOS, LIVE STREAMING AUDIO RECEIVER " Link irec}

     AudioLabs announces iRec (internet Recording), live streaming MPEG
     capabilities for AmigaOS! This cool feature comes embedded in any new
     ProStationAudio version, starting with the forthcoming Millennium edition.

   * @{" PHOTOFOLIO 2 HAS BEEN RELEASED! " Link photo}

     PhotoFolio is the professional solution for anyone wishing to catalogue,
     view, or store images. Different sort modes, gamma correction, any number
     of browse windows and much more make this software an absolute highlight
     of its class.

   * @{" CONTENTS OF THE AMIGA ACTIVE ISSUE 6 " Link aactive}

     Amiga Active is a very good magazine which was born from the CU-Amiga
     ashes. Its latest issue is now on sale, and these are its contents.

   * @{" MET@BOX NEWS " Link metabox}

     The german magazine "amigaOS" has published in its latest issue an
     interview with Thomas Rudloff (met@box). Martin Heine (of amiga-news.de
     fame) has posted some of the answers in c.s.a.misc and here you have them.

   * @{" AMIGAOS 3.5 HIDDEN MESSAGES " Link os35}

     Two days ago Harry Sintonen happened to browse to Workbench Nostalgia web
     page just to find out that seemingly no one has yet found the AmigaOS 3.5
     hidden message. Olaf Barthel has confirmed there is one so he did some
     studies and found it.

   * @{" VOTE IN THE AAA AWARDS - NOW WITH NEW CATEGORIES! " Link aaa}

     Here's a fresh press release from the AAA Awards. This year's public voting
     have been opened now officially and this year there are some changes:
     easier procedure, a new Product award and a new award region: the USA!

   * @{" PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART VIII " Link apex}

     Now that the Payback engine is 90% complete, James Daniels have started to
     turn his attention to designing the levels, which means he haven't got as
     many new features to report as usual. Anyway, here's what's been added to
     the game this month.

   * @{" AMINET 35 HAS BEEN RELEASED! " Link aminet}

     Aminet CD 35, dated February 2000, contains 1 gigabyte (uncompressed) of
     software in thousands of archives. Since the release of Aminet CD 34 more
     than 500 MB new software has appeared. The current edition features the a
     special edition of Digital Almanac II.

   * @{" OPEN AMIGA FOUNDATION AND AROS ANNOUNCE STRATEGIC RELATIONSHIP " Link oaf}

     The Open Amiga Foundation and AROS are to enter into a strategic
     relationship which they believe will be of great benefit to their
     organisations, their members and the wider Amiga community. In the words
     of Open Amiga president Steve Crietzman, "our objectives are compatible,
     it makes sense for us to work together."

   * @{" LIST OF FORTHCOMING AMIGA/PC DUAL CD GAMES BY CRYSTAL INTERACTIVE " Link crystal}

     Crystal Interactive recently announced the conversion of the big hit
     Pokemon for Amiga/PC: This is the list of forthcoming Amiga/PC dual games
     to be released for this clever company.

   * @{" RANDOMIZE UPDATE - FEB 11, 2000 " Link random}

     According to this letter from Canadian distributor Randomize, it is
     rumoured that most of Phase5's engineers have been hired by Metabox for
     the AmiJoe project. So, all hope is not lost and we expecting a G3 or G4
     accelerator line to be coming from Metabox.

   * @{" AMIGA INC., AND HAAGE & PARTNER ANNOUNCE A PATH TOWARDS THE FUTURE " Link haage}

     Amiga Inc and Haage & Partner are pleased to announce a full and long term
     strategic partnership designed to benefit both the classic Amiga, and the
     Amigas of the future.

   * @{" WORLD OF AMIGA 2000 " Link woa2k}

     Once again, the UK will be the centre of Amiga attention this summer. While
     we are awaiting confirmation of the exact dates, we can confirm that the
     show will be happening in late June/early July.

   * @{" FAX FROM PHASE 5 DATED 02/09/2000 14.43 H " Link phase5}

     On January 26., 2000 application for insolvency was made about the property
     of phase 5 digital products, and the application proceedings has been
     established by a decee made by the competent county court at the same day.

   * @{" CLICKBOOM S-FILES: PART III " Link clickboom}

     The lovely Sofia, from clickBOOM, has seen the alpha version of Nightlong
     for Amigam and according to her, it was going to be a great game. So,
     preorder now!

   * @{" ERIOL USB STATUS: 5TH FEBRUARY 2000 " Link eriol}

     Trigertronics is designing a USB card (named Eriol) for Amiga. This is the
     latest status report.

   * @{" INTERVIEW WITH THOMAS DELLERT, DCE " Link dce}

     Thomas Dellert answers some sensitive questions about the Phase 5
     bankruptcy and the future of the PPC product developed by the Oberusel
     company.

   * @{" NEWS FROM EPIC " Link epic}

     These are the Latest Amiga News from Epic Marketing. The most interesting
     piece of news is that Simon the Sorcerer 2 is still on schedule and a
     release date will be annnounced later this month.

   * @{" DIGITAL IMAGES JOB VACANCY " Link digital}

     There is currently a job vacancy for a C++ programmer to work on Space
     Station 3000. You will require knowledge with GUI programming and AI.

   * @{" DARKAGE SOFTWARE NEWS " Link darkage}

     These are the latest news from italian developers Darkage Software, makers
     of Tales From Heaven and Extreme.

   * @{" REGARDING QUESTIONS TO VILLAGE TRONIC PRODUCTS FOR AMIGA - A SHORT REPORT " Link village}

     Village Tronic, the makers of the excellent Picasso IV multimedia boards,
     are alive, and the Paraglide project as well.

   * @{" MORPHOS PROJECT STATUS " Link morphos}

     The highly expected MorphOS developer package won't make it this month.

   * @{" BURNIT V2.65 HAS BEEN RELEASED " Link burnit}

     A new version of BurnIt, the first and only Amiga CD-Recording package
     which supports DAO 2448 Mode, well known as CD+G copy mode, is now
     available.

   * @{" ALIVE: QUAKE PPC NEWS " Link alive}

     Since Xmas, Alive have been announcing details of the imminent release of
     Quake PPC. To keep you updated, I'm please to say that the work is
     progressing very well. Alive will soon be able to start bundling Amiga
     Quake with this new version.

   * @{" AMICOMSYS 1.31 RELEASED " Link acs}

     A new version of the Amiga communication system AmiComSys has been
     released.
