@node apex "PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART VIII"
                        PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART VIII
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

23 February 2000 - The Latest News

Now that the game engine in 90% complete, I've started to turn my attention to
designing the levels, which means I haven't got as many new features to report
as usual. Anyway, here's what's been added to the game this month:

   * Vehicles now leave behind skidmarks when you slide them - check out the
     latest screenshots at http://www.apex-designs.net/payback_screens.html to
     see what I mean.
   * A system has been implemented which allows certain events to trigger
     others. For example, it's now possible for the game to impose a time limit
     on how long a certain mission should take.
   * The textures used before were really just placeholders - I've started to
     introduce more professional versions, as can be seen in the new
     screenshots at http://www.apex-designs.net/payback_screens.html.
   * If you start to kill people then the police will respond by shooting you on
     sight. They'll also put up roadblocks and try to run you over.
   * Lots of new sound effects have been added to the game - buses beep as they
     reverse, people scream when you run them over, crowds cheer when you
     complete a mission and grenades make a 'clink' noise when they bounce -
     which can be very helpful if you're not the one who threw the grenade!

Well, that's it for this update - look forward to seeing you next time!

James Daniels
Apex Designs

For more information about Payback, visit
http://www.apex-designs.net/payback.html.
