Snoqualmie Ridge Business Park

Activity at the business park gains momentum with the addition of another
high-tech tenant

BELLEVUE, Wash. - February 29, 2000 - Growth continues at Snoqualmie Ridge
Business Park with the arrival of the newest high-tech tenant, Amiga, Inc. The
Quadrant Corporation, developer of the business park, announced that Amiga will
move its world headquarters to Snoqualmie Ridge on March 1.

Amiga created and developed the world's first multi-media computer system in the
early 1980s. It continues the development, design and implementation of
components, services, and models that support the digital experience of the
future. Amiga's products are used by companies such as Walt Disney Co., Warner
Bros. and NASA.

The company will occupy 10,100 square feet in a building owned by The Inception
Group. Eventually, Amiga will house 70 employees at its headquarters.

"Snoqualmie Ridge Business Park offers value and unique benefits for Amiga,"
said Bill McEwen, president of Amiga. "Not only does it provide great
flexibility for growth, but it also offers open and serene surroundings for our
employees."

"Not many locations provide an environment where you can write code while
looking out the window at wildlife and a great view of Mt. Si," added McEwen.

Located less than 20 minutes from downtown Bellevue on I-90, Snoqualmie Ridge
Business Park is the largest available business park in East King County. Amiga
joins other high tech companies such as Optiva, manufacturer of the Sonicare
Toothbrush, and The Inception Group. The business park's Cascade View office
building currently has 28,650 square feet of available space.

Brokers for the deal were Dave Miller of Raskin & Associates for The Inception
Group and Steve Oswald and Ann Bishop of Wallace Properties representing Amiga.

Quadrant's Commercial Division has developed more than five million square feet
of commercial space in more than 80 building projects in the Puget Sound
metropolitan area. Visit Quadrant's Web site at http://www.quadrantcorp.com/.
