--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

More best of breed technology for networked digital appliances exclusive to the
intent(TM) brand

Reading, England, February 17th 2000.

The Tao Group has today provided further proof of its continuing drive and
success in making its intent(TM) digital content engine and toolkit the very
best the industry can offer in terms of quality, footprint, performance,
flexibility, and portability. This has come in the form of the announcement of
Tao's intent Font System. intent is Tao's binary portable applications layer for
networked digital appliances, combining the most advanced technologies for an
integrated Java(TM) language, C and portable assembler environment. intent also
consolidates audio with both 2D and 3D graphics in one complete package. It is
available across most market leading operating systems and almost the complete
range of major processor families for consumer products.

Tao had already revealed details of its own 2D drawing, windowing, compositing
and gadget libraries, the integration of Criterion's RenderWare® 3D solution and
the SSEYO(TM) Koan(TM) audio engine as part of the intent digital content
platform. As reported last month, Francis Charig, Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer of Tao told analysts, "intent is so named because we are putting
together the leading multimedia technologies for the creation of compelling
interactive content. In spite of strong demand there has been an industry vacuum
in this area, that intent is now filling."

Tao has now released the details of the intent font system, which Tao executives
believe will further position its software as the standard content foundation
for networked digital appliances.

The Font System consists of three layers: glyph caching technology, vector
rendering engine and format decoder plug-ins. It has achieved an impressive
roll-call of objectives: including having a low memory footprint, high
performance, and high readability. It is customer extendable, the system has
flexible configuration options and it is fully platform independent.

Plug-ins include TrueType®, PostScript® Type 1, Windows® Resource Fonts and ROM
Fonts with additional plug-in options to follow.

Features include 1 bit, 4 bit or 8 bit anti-aliasing, on-the-fly gamma
correction, configurable cache memory, configurable font name mapping,
Panose(TM) matching, Micro-spaced printing, co-existing plug-ins, and it has a
typical footprint of 50KB.

The font engine enables high quality rendering, with on-screen easy readability,
even on low-end consumer devices and yet can scale up to the highest quality DTP
typographical requirements.

The font system is an essential component of the development kit to be announced
shortly by Tao and its partners. Further announcements of world class tools for
the intent engine will be made shortly.

For more information about RenderWare, please see http://www.renderware.com/

