---| EDITORIAL |-----------------------------------------| LARGER THAN LIFE |---
    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                                           ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Hello and welcome to the 19th issue of AmiChannel News.

If you are connected to the Internet, probably you already know the bad news.
Phase 5, manufacturers of the PowerUp boards and 3D Gfx cards for Amiga is now
out of business.

This is a sad news, but a clear indication of the total death of hardware
development for Amiga. Yes, some games and applications are still being
developed for Amiga, but not a real hardware product, perhaps with the exception
of the AmiJoe boards.

Phase 5 tried to revitalize the Amiga with the release of PPC boards and 3D Gfx
cards for the Amiga. They did a great job but they made two big errors.

As you probably remember, the kernel war between Phase 5 and Haage&Partner in
1997 hurted a lot to Phase 5. The big problem was that Phase 5 tried to do
everything (hardware and software) when they were only a hardware company. If
they had collaborated with H&P using the WarpUp kernel is the PowerUp boards,
they would have succeed.

The second mistake was to stop the production of PowerUp boards so they have not
a damn product in market while they were developing the G4 boards. So, they had
not an income and the final result was their bankruptcy. A shame, but life goes
on.

